  "prompt": "What is indexing?",
  "response": "Indexing is the process of organizing and storing data in a way that makes it easier to retrieve and access. This can be done in various contexts, such as in databases, search engines, and file systems. The goal of indexing is to improve the speed and efficiency of data retrieval by creating an organized structure, or index, that allows for quick searching and sorting of the data. In a database, for example, an index can be created on one or more columns of a table to speed up queries that search, filter, or sort based on those columns. In a search engine, indexing involves analyzing and storing the contents of web pages so that they can be quickly retrieved in response to a user's query.",
